commentary: Junaid Khan to Soumya Sarkar, OUT out for a duck on comeback, and that's very well bowled. He's been bringing him forward with his lengths so far, and he digs this one in short, and outside off stump. Gets it up to shoulder height, and Soumya is in no position to control his pull. Ends up skying it and offering a simple catch to square leg. Mohammad Amir has been struggling for wickets, and his replacement strikes in his second over

commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Mominul Haque, OUT and he follows up with a beaut and beats Mominul for pace! Back of a length, pitches outside off and nips back in off the track, skids off the wicket and Mominul is late bringing his bat down in defence. Didn't really matter, because it would have beaten his inside edge anyway. Cannons off the back pad and leaves his off stump spinning. Pakistan's left-arm quicks are on fire here

commentary: Mohammad Nawaz to Mohammad Mithun, no run big appeal after he strikes the pad with an arm ball, not given out. Seemed to be heading down leg, and Pakistan make a late decision to review after a long consultation between bowler and keeper/captain... The length trapped him on the crease in defence, and the lack of turn beat the inside edge, but that's a shocking review. The ball has struck his pad outside leg stump!

commentary: Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Asif Ali, OUT ooh, that's superb glovework to follow a beauty of a delivery. Classic offspinner's dismissal, lovely flight outside off and it's the one that drifts away slightly and continues along that trajectory after pitching. Draws Asif forward, makes him reach for the ball, and in the process causes him to lift his back foot out of the crease. Liton collects and removes the bails in one motion, and Bangladesh are back on top once more
